{
  "texts": [
    "We used the following performance metrics for susceptibility and the area density components.",
    "To evaluate the model's performance during the training process and the inference, we used two common metrics, namely the F1 score (Meena et al., 2022; Nava et al., 2022) and the Intersection over Union (IOU) score (e.g., Huang et al., 2019; Ghorbanzadeh et al., 2020).",
    "We did not use binary accuracy because it is heavily influenced by data imbalance (Yeon et al., 2010; Li et al., 2022) and can produce high accuracy, even for poor classifications.",
    "The F1 score is calculated as:",
    "where TP denotes the True Positives, FP denotes the False Positives, TN denotes the True Negatives, and FN denotes the False Negatives in the confusion matrix."
  ]
}